1
00:01:17,985 --> 00:01:19,353
Jo, are you ready?

2
00:01:19,354 --> 00:01:22,322
Hey, baby. No, no - um...
Yes, I'm all set.

3
00:01:22,615 --> 00:01:24,115
Why don't you get something to eat?

4
00:01:25,868 --> 00:01:27,368
Jo, we're already late.

5
00:01:45,973 --> 00:01:47,516
Did you grab a bottle of wine?

6
00:02:08,037 --> 00:02:11,206
If we get hitten, you could lose an eye.

7
00:02:15,169 --> 00:02:16,920
Not today.

8
00:02:18,923 --> 00:02:20,674
How was your day?

9
00:02:21,692 --> 00:02:23,075
My day was fine.

10
00:02:32,772 --> 00:02:34,139
Thank you.

11
00:02:39,696 --> 00:02:41,822
Michael where's the wine?
What?

12
00:02:41,948 --> 00:02:45,117
Wine.
Shit!

13
00:02:49,914 --> 00:02:51,819
Wait, wait, wait...

14
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,625
Hello!

15
00:02:56,838 --> 00:02:58,922
You look nice baby.
Thanks.

16
00:03:03,178 --> 00:03:04,519
Come.

17
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,351
I love you.

18
00:03:17,878 --> 00:03:20,547
Oh, you didn't bring Sarah?
You didn't tell her?

19
00:03:20,673 --> 00:03:23,070
See you in hour.
You should be finished by then.

20
00:03:23,071 --> 00:03:24,467
Oh well, thank you for that!

21
00:03:25,094 --> 00:03:27,387
Barbara! Hello!
Thanks for having us.

22
00:03:27,513 --> 00:03:29,180
Come see me upstairs.
I will.

23
00:03:29,974 --> 00:03:32,767
How long were you two together?
Three months.

24
00:03:32,893 --> 00:03:35,603
Three months?
Three months already?

25
00:03:36,439 --> 00:03:40,066
Talking to Monroe, I think we should schedule
another meeting for Monday.

26
00:03:41,110 --> 00:03:42,652
Okay, let's just see how tomorrow goes.

27
00:03:42,678 --> 00:03:46,130
I bet you didn't like Sarah either, did you?
I did! I said I did!

28
00:03:46,156 --> 00:03:47,824
Yeah, but I don't think that you meant it.

29
00:03:49,902 --> 00:03:51,302
Thanks.
Welcome.

30
00:03:51,328 --> 00:03:52,745
Why's it so hard for me, Jo?

31
00:03:52,871 --> 00:03:56,207
It isn't. I mean it can't be.
You haven't gone to the hard bit yet.

32
00:03:56,231 --> 00:03:57,792
What it gets harder than this?
- Joanna?

33
00:03:57,918 --> 00:04:00,378
Hello!
Hi, so good to see you.

34
00:04:00,504 --> 00:04:02,255
Thank you for having us.

35
00:04:02,381 --> 00:04:03,798
Andy...
Stuart...

36
00:04:06,151 --> 00:04:08,470
Michael says you're working on a new book.

37
00:04:08,570 --> 00:04:10,015
Michael always says that.

38
00:04:10,516 --> 00:04:11,891
He's probably right.

39
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:14,936
I just don't know it?

40
00:04:17,148 --> 00:04:19,320
Well, I got to go and talk to somebody.

41
00:04:19,321 --> 00:04:20,692
Eat, I'll be here.

42
00:04:20,702 --> 00:04:22,494
He hates me.
He's gonna fire me. I know.

43
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:24,571
You say that every week.
Yeah well, it's true.

44
00:04:24,572 --> 00:04:26,323
But it hasn't been in the last two years.

45
00:04:26,324 --> 00:04:28,193
Well maybe he's just waiting for the right time.

46
00:04:28,194 --> 00:04:30,785
Hey do you want me to walk Lucy,
while you guys are away?

47
00:04:30,811 --> 00:04:32,329
Yeah, that'd be great.

48
00:04:32,455 --> 00:04:34,748
Where is Michael anyway?

49
00:04:36,157 --> 00:04:37,467
Here he is.

50
00:04:38,555 --> 00:04:39,868
Here he is, let's go!

51
00:04:40,921 --> 00:04:43,840
Joanna?
Um yes no I'm going to go to the ladies.

52
00:04:43,841 --> 00:04:46,760
I'll catch you up.
Okay.

53
00:05:12,665 --> 00:05:15,416
I'm starving.

54
00:05:18,086 --> 00:05:21,130
Hey, where have you guys been?
I got totally ambushed by Stuart.

55
00:05:21,131 --> 00:05:22,751
The guy's hasn't talked to me in two weeks -

56
00:05:22,758 --> 00:05:24,967
- and sees me with your wife,
and just lit up.

57
00:05:28,931 --> 00:05:31,583
Laura, this is my Joanna.
Hello! Nice to meet you.

58
00:05:31,584 --> 00:05:34,343
Joanna, this is Laura. She's our new designer,
who has worked for us.

59
00:05:34,769 --> 00:05:36,521
Nice to finally meet you.

60
00:05:36,947 --> 00:05:39,440
So Michael tells me you're a writer.
Yes, I am.

61
00:05:39,566 --> 00:05:42,777
I've been meaning to order your book.
That's nice.

62
00:05:42,903 --> 00:05:46,447
Oh! Look, look! Oh my god!
Neal he's trying with Cynthia again.

63
00:05:46,448 --> 00:05:48,950
She's not going to go for it.
I know. It just won't work.

64
00:05:48,951 --> 00:05:50,442
Why not?
He's a good looking guy.

65
00:05:51,044 --> 00:05:53,079
Why did you turn him down?

66
00:05:53,105 --> 00:05:54,430
Speak of the devil...

67
00:05:54,456 --> 00:05:56,549
Hey, Neal!
Had any luck with Cynthia?

68
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:58,350
Hi Joanna!
Hello.

69
00:05:58,351 --> 00:05:59,951
Had any luck?
What?

70
00:06:00,921 --> 00:06:03,131
You didn't really go to
"The Yogo" with her, did you?

71
00:06:03,841 --> 00:06:06,176
She told you that?
She told me about that!

72
00:06:06,202 --> 00:06:09,762
Still with Cynthia huh?
What? You're getting jealous?

73
00:06:10,889 --> 00:06:13,683
So what's Laura's story?

74
00:06:13,809 --> 00:06:16,936
Stuart recruited her.
She seems to be good.

75
00:06:15,290 --> 00:06:18,375
She's working the Monroe project with us.

76
00:06:20,876 --> 00:06:22,461
Of course she is...

77
00:06:27,145 --> 00:06:29,070
Try to get me some wine?

78
00:06:44,468 --> 00:06:46,260
That's not funny.

79
00:06:54,475 --> 00:06:57,154
There you go.
Hi. Would you like a drink?

80
00:06:57,181 --> 00:06:59,582
Yeah, white wine please.
Sure.

81
00:07:01,109 --> 00:07:02,485
Thanks.

82
00:07:03,405 --> 00:07:05,802
Is she going to Philadelphia with you guys tomorrow?

83
00:07:06,203 --> 00:07:07,600
Yeah.

84
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:11,329
And she was in LA with
Michael last month?

85
00:07:20,631 --> 00:07:22,173
Taxi!

86
00:07:25,928 --> 00:07:27,428
Have you been smoking?

87
00:07:29,097 --> 00:07:31,808
You really going to attempt to give me
a grief about that?

88
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,450
What's wrong?

89
00:07:35,252 --> 00:07:36,602
Nothing.

90
00:07:40,716 --> 00:07:42,300
Have I done something wrong?

91
00:08:44,554 --> 00:08:46,601
She is pretty.
Who?

92
00:08:48,411 --> 00:08:50,066
You never mentioned that.

93
00:08:50,067 --> 00:08:52,122
Laura?
Yeah, Laura.

94
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,292
I think you described her as "whatever".

95
00:08:55,877 --> 00:08:58,337
I don't remember.
I bet.

96
00:09:04,219 --> 00:09:06,470
You didn't tell me that she was in LA with you.

97
00:09:06,596 --> 00:09:09,014
She's wasn't in LA with me.
We were just there at the same time.

98
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,683
Michael, face me!

99
00:09:11,768 --> 00:09:15,312
You didn't tell me anything about her, before tonight,
but then I think you know that.

100
00:09:15,647 --> 00:09:17,106
What's that supposed to mean?

101
00:09:18,566 --> 00:09:20,985
What did you think could happen tonight?

102
00:09:21,444 --> 00:09:24,363
And seriously, did you think I just wouldn't notice?

103
00:09:24,823 --> 00:09:27,032
Why would I think anything would make you notice her?

104
00:09:27,242 --> 00:09:29,034
You're a terrible liar!

105
00:09:29,205 --> 00:09:30,786
Might be because
I don't I lie.

106
00:09:30,912 --> 00:09:33,122
She likes you,
and you like her.

107
00:09:33,123 --> 00:09:35,623
Of course you don't want to talk to me
about it.

108
00:09:36,025 --> 00:09:38,342
Where is this come from?
My eyes, Michael!

109
00:09:38,543 --> 00:09:41,043
She's she the only one you talked to,
all night.

110
00:09:41,323 --> 00:09:43,382
How many glasses of wine did you have
tonight, Jo?

111
00:09:43,408 --> 00:09:46,210
Two and two sips.
Is that really your response?

112
00:09:46,236 --> 00:09:47,745
You had more than that.

113
00:09:47,771 --> 00:09:50,180
What are you?
The drink patrol?

114
00:09:50,306 --> 00:09:53,392
Well remind me when we go out,
and I ask you not to have another.

115
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:55,936
You ask me why.
This is why.

116
00:09:56,062 --> 00:09:59,481
You're kidding me, right?
Because it makes you like this, baby.

117
00:10:01,026 --> 00:10:04,486
Michael without wine we would be in a
much shittier place.

118
00:10:05,096 --> 00:10:08,282
Eleven hours a day.
Five, sometimes six days a week.

119
00:10:08,408 --> 00:10:12,911
That's sixty hours a week with her,
three months now.

120
00:10:13,371 --> 00:10:17,916
What is it you think I have done?
Check my phone, Jo.

121
00:10:18,209 --> 00:10:20,411
And check my e-mails, check receipts, go on.

122
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:23,088
Not everyone gets caught, Michael.

123
00:10:25,341 --> 00:10:27,301
Has she told you she's attracted to you?

124
00:10:27,635 --> 00:10:29,386
Maybe, Joanna.

125
00:10:29,888 --> 00:10:32,347
I don't let the conversation go there.

126
00:10:32,474 --> 00:10:34,266
But she tried to, hasn't she?

127
00:10:34,392 --> 00:10:37,019
But she tried to when you were
in LA together?

128
00:10:37,145 --> 00:10:40,189
You do hours I do not know about,
with the people that you work with.

129
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:42,900
You go away -

130
00:10:43,151 --> 00:10:46,487
doing articles, all the time!

131
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:53,118
Have I ever given you a reason to stand here
feeling the way that I am right now?

132
00:10:54,079 --> 00:10:58,065
I looked through a window tonight and I
saw something that I didn't need to see.

133
00:10:58,091 --> 00:11:00,054
Couldn't you just have watched yourself
and spared me?

134
00:11:00,055 --> 00:11:01,418
What the fuck are you doing!?

135
00:11:01,419 --> 00:11:04,354
I want to charge the phone.
Why do you always have to use this one?

136
00:10:58,380 --> 00:11:00,924
Why did you build a Berlin wall of freakin' magazines!?

137
00:11:03,719 --> 00:11:08,139
I haven't done anything wrong,
and you try to pick a fight.

138
00:11:09,850 --> 00:11:11,392
I spare you.

139
00:11:17,149 --> 00:11:18,541
I would.

140
00:11:23,197 --> 00:11:24,886
What's that supposed to mean?

141
00:11:26,887 --> 00:11:28,576
What's that supposed to mean?

142
00:11:31,288 --> 00:11:34,424
Is she going to Philadelphia
with you and Andy tomorrow?

143
00:11:34,684 --> 00:11:36,876
Uh-huh, cause she's been working on
the Monroe properly with us.

144
00:11:38,546 --> 00:11:40,421
Why? What does that look?

145
00:11:41,901 --> 00:11:43,422
That looks sad, Michael.

146
00:11:44,009 --> 00:11:47,303
There's nothing going on, Jo.
Laura is just someone I work with.

147
00:11:49,598 --> 00:11:53,567
It's not that I'm blaming you for being
attracted to her. She's... -

148
00:11:53,568 --> 00:11:54,936
attractive.

149
00:11:56,313 --> 00:12:00,400
And it's natural to crave newness.

150
00:12:08,576 --> 00:12:10,160
So what are you blaming me for?

151
00:12:11,537 --> 00:12:13,872
For going out of your way not to admit it.

152
00:12:16,458 --> 00:12:18,501
Thought I just did.

153
00:12:22,506 --> 00:12:24,716
Don't do that face, Jo...

154
00:12:31,265 --> 00:12:33,099
You know what I meant.

155
00:12:35,352 --> 00:12:38,229
You corner me, and you order me
to admit something -

156
00:12:38,355 --> 00:12:40,400
and then you're pouncing me the second I came,
and now you're going to sleep on the couch?

157
00:12:40,776 --> 00:12:42,360
Fucking fantastic!

158
00:12:44,614 --> 00:12:46,656
I did not do anything wrong, Jo.

159
00:13:12,062 --> 00:13:13,520
I'm sorry.

160
00:13:15,607 --> 00:13:16,941
What for?

161
00:13:18,109 --> 00:13:21,695
I'm not sure but,
I love you.

162
00:13:23,031 --> 00:13:24,423
Come to bed.

163
00:13:25,492 --> 00:13:26,909
I don't want to.

164
00:13:31,414 --> 00:13:33,123
Come to the kitchen.

165
00:13:33,375 --> 00:13:35,167
Food isn't going to fix this.

166
00:13:35,293 --> 00:13:37,427
Soon you'll have a full stomach.
Come on.

167
00:13:40,131 --> 00:13:42,883
We got any tomatoes?
No.

168
00:14:02,572 --> 00:14:04,031
How was your day?

169
00:14:04,157 --> 00:14:07,410
Oh, but...

170
00:14:08,912 --> 00:14:11,539
What?
Nothing, I just remembered I'm mad at you.

171
00:14:11,665 --> 00:14:13,249
I hate it when that happens.

172
00:14:15,877 --> 00:14:17,415
Danny proposed!

173
00:14:17,416 --> 00:14:18,754
Yeah!

174
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:21,299
What Pia said?
What did you think she said? Yes!

175
00:14:21,325 --> 00:14:22,666
Was she surprised at all?

176
00:14:22,692 --> 00:14:25,177
Yes, she thought that he was going to tell her
he was moving out.

177
00:14:36,106 --> 00:14:39,400
My mum called.
Yeah, I know. I spoked to her.

178
00:14:40,152 --> 00:14:43,072
Second week of December.
I've already said yes.

179
00:14:44,698 --> 00:14:47,742
Can we go via London?
Yeah, sure.

180
00:14:50,787 --> 00:14:53,497
What time is your train?
At 8:00.

181
00:14:53,623 --> 00:14:55,708
You shouldn't be up this late.

182
00:14:55,834 --> 00:14:57,251
I'll sleep on the train.

183
00:14:57,252 --> 00:15:00,226
It's an hours ride.
I'll sleep in the meeting.

184
00:15:02,132 --> 00:15:04,133
What are you doing tomorrow or today?

185
00:15:04,593 --> 00:15:06,586
I got to finish up the accessories piece.

186
00:15:06,587 --> 00:15:08,279
Yeah, with pearls?

187
00:15:08,305 --> 00:15:11,057
Yeah, I'll dig up another hundred words.

188
00:15:11,183 --> 00:15:14,094
It's good. And then you can work on the book,
without me here to distract you.

189
00:15:18,276 --> 00:15:19,818
Joanna, I'm sorry.

190
00:15:20,445 --> 00:15:23,781
I would have said something about her,
if I thought there was something to say.

191
00:15:26,576 --> 00:15:29,027
Michael, did something happen in LA?

192
00:15:29,028 --> 00:15:30,379
No.

193
00:15:33,083 --> 00:15:35,501
I swear.
No.

194
00:15:39,506 --> 00:15:41,006
Eggs are good.

195
00:15:43,426 --> 00:15:44,802
Yeah.

196
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,523
What about the orange juice?

197
00:15:57,824 --> 00:15:59,566
Come on.
What kind of cafe is this?

198
00:16:07,702 --> 00:16:09,995
Do you think we got married too soon?

199
00:16:13,834 --> 00:16:15,160
What?

200
00:16:15,661 --> 00:16:18,087
Why can't you make yourself consider that?

201
00:16:20,048 --> 00:16:21,757
Because I don't have to.

202
00:16:23,385 --> 00:16:25,428
I don't think we got married too soon -

203
00:16:25,554 --> 00:16:27,596
because we married after four years.

204
00:16:27,722 --> 00:16:30,141
Yeah, with a break up in the middle.

205
00:16:30,851 --> 00:16:33,894
And anyway, it's not about the amount of time
but the when of time -

206
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:36,897
and our when included college.

207
00:16:38,459 --> 00:16:40,998
You know, that was before we were even us, you know.

208
00:16:43,822 --> 00:16:46,991
Do you think it's even the same
between us?

209
00:16:48,827 --> 00:16:51,036
It got better...

210
00:16:53,955 --> 00:16:56,750
Can you hear yourself right now?

211
00:16:59,588 --> 00:17:00,921
What?

212
00:17:01,847 --> 00:17:06,385
Just because I disagree with you,
means I'm not aware of what I'm saying?

213
00:17:06,511 --> 00:17:08,345
You can't really think that.

214
00:17:08,722 --> 00:17:11,390
I do think that.
How?

215
00:17:11,725 --> 00:17:15,060
Sunday night.
The last two weekends.

216
00:17:15,187 --> 00:17:17,980
Breakfast yesterday.
Dinner last night.

217
00:17:18,190 --> 00:17:20,191
There's no bullshit between us.

218
00:17:22,527 --> 00:17:24,778
With the possible exception of this evening.

219
00:17:29,951 --> 00:17:32,703
Come here, Jo.
I'm cold.

220
00:18:32,894 --> 00:18:38,190
Got your orange juice?
No. Thank you!

221
00:19:01,214 --> 00:19:04,383
You're gonna try to get some writing done?
"Try" is a big word.

222
00:19:04,509 --> 00:19:05,859
No, it's not.

223
00:19:06,806 --> 00:19:10,601
Alright, I got to go.
See you later.

224
00:19:11,394 --> 00:19:12,728
Bye.

225
00:20:17,003 --> 00:20:19,004
Hello.
A cup of coffee, please.

226
00:20:33,313 --> 00:20:34,663
Joanna!

227
00:20:39,277 --> 00:20:41,779
Alex! What are you doing here?

228
00:20:41,905 --> 00:20:43,280
I have some work here.

229
00:20:46,574 --> 00:20:47,993
I can't believe this!

230
00:20:48,245 --> 00:20:50,955
Yeah, it's been a while.
How are you?

231
00:20:51,123 --> 00:20:56,043
I'm fine, I just can't believe you're here.
How did you know I'd be here?

232
00:20:56,169 --> 00:20:57,862
I keep tabs on you.

233
00:20:57,863 --> 00:20:59,755
I'm serious.
So am I.

234
00:21:01,133 --> 00:21:04,301
Your Christmas cards.
They gave the return address on them.

235
00:21:04,428 --> 00:21:07,221
What if I'd moved?
You haven't.

236
00:21:08,515 --> 00:21:10,391
How long are you in New York for?

237
00:21:10,517 --> 00:21:13,894
I leave tomorrow. Actually, I'm late for a meeting.

238
00:21:15,522 --> 00:21:17,314
Do you have time for me now?

239
00:21:18,066 --> 00:21:21,277
Yeah, yeah. Sure.
Good.

240
00:21:21,403 --> 00:21:24,029
Then I call you later with the time.

241
00:21:24,156 --> 00:21:26,657
Wait, wait, do you need my number?
Has it changed?

242
00:21:27,868 --> 00:21:29,243
No...

243
00:21:29,870 --> 00:21:31,495
Then I call you later?

244
00:21:34,374 --> 00:21:35,833
Wait!

245
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,300
Cause I've never been able to sleep -

246
00:22:07,301 --> 00:22:10,102
- think that by the time I sleep I won't wake up
for about four years.

247
00:22:10,128 --> 00:22:12,005
Be like...

248
00:22:13,257 --> 00:22:15,252
I need to use the men's room.
Okay.

249
00:22:15,389 --> 00:22:17,719
Michael, we have to wait for Andy.

250
00:22:18,661 --> 00:22:21,950
It's funny, because I could actually...
I could sleep anywhere.

251
00:22:21,982 --> 00:22:24,371
Is that right?
Yes, I could probably fall sleep right here.

252
00:22:24,372 --> 00:22:25,760
