00:40:40,509 --> 00:40:44,178
I didn't move.
I wouldn't have.

511
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,625
I'm married.

512
00:41:06,751 --> 00:41:08,118
I know.

513
00:41:10,707 --> 00:41:12,242
Still it felt nice.

514
00:41:17,996 --> 00:41:21,709
That is so embarrassing!
Thank you.

515
00:41:22,067 --> 00:41:23,989
Usually she's doing it better.

516
00:41:23,990 --> 00:41:26,312
No, the point was that I love Italy.

517
00:41:26,438 --> 00:41:30,024
I love it there.
We have a place, we go there -

518
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:33,068
- one month a year.
It's so wonderful.

519
00:41:33,069 --> 00:41:35,569
Wait! This is who you went to Italy with?
When?

520
00:41:36,123 --> 00:41:37,732
When I got to Paris early, and -

521
00:41:37,758 --> 00:41:40,451
- your little cousin was staying in the apartment,
till you got back -

522
00:41:40,577 --> 00:41:43,412
and you were away with Patrick and his friends.

523
00:41:43,538 --> 00:41:44,997
Yeah, exactly!
This is them.

524
00:41:46,041 --> 00:41:49,501
That's really so weird!
And you seemed familiar!

525
00:41:50,003 --> 00:41:51,337
How funny.

526
00:41:54,092 --> 00:41:55,968
What if you were married?

527
00:41:57,930 --> 00:42:01,098
Hypotheticals don't do much for me, but...

528
00:42:03,101 --> 00:42:05,144
Probably nothing different.

529
00:42:10,234 --> 00:42:13,110
Are you happy?
With what?

530
00:42:14,655 --> 00:42:17,740
With your marriage.
Yeah.

531
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,301
Very.

532
00:42:23,088 --> 00:42:25,589
You can be happy and still be tempted.

533
00:42:26,091 --> 00:42:27,432
I know.

534
00:42:29,177 --> 00:42:31,136
Just surprised you do.

535
00:42:35,016 --> 00:42:37,601
Have you ever been with someone else
since you've been married?

536
00:42:38,978 --> 00:42:40,354
No.

537
00:42:40,814 --> 00:42:43,482
Have you wanted to be?

538
00:42:46,859 --> 00:42:48,195
What happened?

539
00:42:50,740 --> 00:42:52,491
Think of Joanna.

540
00:42:55,370 --> 00:42:58,080
You regret not doing it?

541
00:43:01,084 --> 00:43:03,836
I'd regret more if I did.

542
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:14,584
You ever cheated on anybody?

543
00:43:15,294 --> 00:43:17,378
Cheated?

544
00:43:17,504 --> 00:43:18,921
Have you?

545
00:43:19,798 --> 00:43:21,123
No.

546
00:43:22,676 --> 00:43:25,720
Not necessarily on principle,
I just -

547
00:43:26,013 --> 00:43:27,471
I never wanted to.

548
00:43:32,019 --> 00:43:35,896
Alex, I know you want them.
I need one yeah.

549
00:43:37,941 --> 00:43:39,358
And I know you want one.

550
00:43:39,484 --> 00:43:42,278
No, no, no.
She wants to keep me company.

551
00:43:42,279 --> 00:43:44,847
I do. I do.
You do? I do.

552
00:43:46,199 --> 00:43:47,575
Okay.
So have a good night.

553
00:43:49,076 --> 00:43:51,080
It's a trap.
I know.

554
00:43:52,081 --> 00:43:54,010
You'll never change.

555
00:43:56,251 --> 00:44:00,921
When was the last time you saw Alex?
Two years ago.

556
00:44:01,131 --> 00:44:02,798
So you know Helen?

557
00:44:04,226 --> 00:44:05,526
Helen?

558
00:44:05,552 --> 00:44:07,678
Alex's girlfriend from Paris.

559
00:44:09,099 --> 00:44:12,602
Well, we are not very good
at keeping touch with -

560
00:44:12,728 --> 00:44:17,148
- the dailies.
We talk when we talk.

561
00:44:18,101 --> 00:44:22,362
She's nice. I don't think he's going
to settle down with her anytime soon.

562
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:26,741
But I don't know that Alex would
ever settle down, with anyone.

563
00:44:27,076 --> 00:44:29,619
He seems more whole,
on his own.

564
00:44:31,497 --> 00:44:33,247
So where is your husband?

565
00:44:33,248 --> 00:44:35,848
He's in Philidelphia on a business trip.

566
00:44:38,295 --> 00:44:39,671
What's he do?

567
00:44:39,797 --> 00:44:41,714
Commercial real estate development -

568
00:44:41,740 --> 00:44:45,385
- but, I don't think this was the question
you wanted to ask.

569
00:44:45,511 --> 00:44:49,097
No, it wasn't.
Go ahead.

570
00:44:49,223 --> 00:44:51,099
I usually tend to go too far.

571
00:44:52,309 --> 00:44:54,018
Okay, warning heard.

572
00:44:53,144 --> 00:44:55,062
Does your husband know Alex?

573
00:44:58,733 --> 00:45:00,150
No.

574
00:45:00,694 --> 00:45:02,903
Does he know of him?
No.

575
00:45:03,655 --> 00:45:07,324
Have I gone too far?
Yeah, maybe, but it's fun!

576
00:45:07,827 --> 00:45:09,828
Why haven't you told him?

577
00:45:12,289 --> 00:45:16,876
I think when you know something like that,
you can't unlearn it.

578
00:45:17,878 --> 00:45:20,171
So there is a something like that.

579
00:45:22,508 --> 00:45:24,676
Are you faithful?
Yes.

580
00:45:27,179 --> 00:45:29,472
Will he forgive you,
if you were not?

581
00:45:30,307 --> 00:45:32,350
He's always said
that he wouldn't.

582
00:45:33,352 --> 00:45:35,186
Does that stop you?

583
00:45:36,939 --> 00:45:39,149
Yeah, probably.

584
00:45:39,775 --> 00:45:42,819
How long were you with Alex together?

585
00:45:42,945 --> 00:45:44,821
We were never really together.

586
00:45:44,947 --> 00:45:48,074
We were more kind of on and off.

587
00:45:48,952 --> 00:45:51,495
You think you'll tell your husband
about tonight?

588
00:45:52,914 --> 00:45:55,708
I don't know.
Tonight is not finished yet.

589
00:46:15,337 --> 00:46:18,148
Remember the last time we were here,
and we got in the wrong car?

590
00:46:18,174 --> 00:46:20,141
When was that?
Remember how far we went before you remembered?

591
00:46:20,142 --> 00:46:22,109
Ten blocks. Hey guys, come on.

592
00:46:22,235 --> 00:46:23,628
Why don't you just drive with us?

593
00:46:23,679 --> 00:46:26,155
Oh shit, Lucy!
Who?

594
00:46:26,281 --> 00:46:29,325
A friend's dog.
I said I'd walk her.

595
00:46:29,451 --> 00:46:30,868
Where is she?

596
00:46:31,244 --> 00:46:32,578
She's on our friend's apartment.

597
00:46:33,455 --> 00:46:35,331
Are you just saying that to get out of
going to the party?

598
00:46:35,457 --> 00:46:37,666
No, No! I know! I swear!

599
00:46:37,003 --> 00:46:39,171
When were you last in New York?

600
00:46:40,465 --> 00:46:42,966
About nine months ago.

601
00:46:43,259 --> 00:46:45,594
Why didn't you get in touch?

602
00:46:47,597 --> 00:46:51,600
I wasn't alone...

603
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:32,042
Can't get the key out!

604
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:06,375
Andy cooks?

605
00:48:06,501 --> 00:48:10,588
No, I bought that for him last year
I doubt he's ever used it.

606
00:48:11,465 --> 00:48:13,216
I do that when we're over.

607
00:48:13,342 --> 00:48:15,384
So why aren't you writing?

608
00:48:16,136 --> 00:48:17,678
I am writing!

609
00:48:17,804 --> 00:48:19,118
No, why aren't you writing?

610
00:48:19,119 --> 00:48:21,432
You mean...
Your book, Joanna.

611
00:48:24,269 --> 00:48:28,564
My editor says that I just need to get over
my doubt.

612
00:48:29,816 --> 00:48:33,277
What do you doubt?
Everything, Alex.

613
00:48:34,488 --> 00:48:37,281
I go to write -

614
00:48:37,407 --> 00:48:41,177
- and every word, every thought, every choice
that I make leads to another and -

615
00:48:41,703 --> 00:48:43,829
I doubt every single one I make.

616
00:48:44,081 --> 00:48:45,873
It wasn't like this last time.

617
00:48:46,575 --> 00:48:49,293
You live with your first book
all your life -

618
00:48:49,919 --> 00:48:51,595
it comes out on its own.

619
00:48:52,839 --> 00:48:56,217
After that though, it's just different.
You can suddenly write -

620
00:48:56,343 --> 00:48:59,929
anything and you second-guess everything.

621
00:49:01,390 --> 00:49:05,977
Doubts will kill your work.
Who me? I don't know.

622
00:49:06,895 --> 00:49:08,813
What's the matter with doubt?

623
00:49:09,356 --> 00:49:11,783
I think the world could use
a little more doubt.

624
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:11,383
So I doubt...

625
00:49:11,409 --> 00:49:13,177
For the good of the world?

626
00:49:13,386 --> 00:49:14,845
Exactly.

627
00:49:15,096 --> 00:49:16,430
No, thank you.

628
00:49:18,391 --> 00:49:20,267
Your first book was good, Joanna.

629
00:49:25,773 --> 00:49:28,150
You know I think you might just have ruined
this kitchen for me.

630
00:49:28,486 --> 00:49:29,874
How?

631
00:49:30,275 --> 00:49:31,863
By being in it.

632
00:49:34,450 --> 00:49:36,993
I come here all the time,
and now you've been here.

633
00:49:49,815 --> 00:49:52,008
Remind me why it didn't work?

634
00:49:52,885 --> 00:49:54,227
Geography.

635
00:49:54,228 --> 00:49:55,970
People live between two cities.

636
00:49:56,180 --> 00:49:58,097
I don't, and neither do you.

637
00:49:59,308 --> 00:50:00,683
And timing.

638
00:50:00,809 --> 00:50:02,352
You were broken up!

639
00:50:02,770 --> 00:50:06,731
Temporarily. Technically, whateverly...

640
00:50:06,857 --> 00:50:08,191
We got back together -

641
00:50:08,317 --> 00:50:11,319
- after we'd already been together
for a really long time.

642
00:50:11,820 --> 00:50:13,404
You came after.

643
00:50:13,531 --> 00:50:17,534
So you're with him,
because he came first?

644
00:50:17,826 --> 00:50:20,495
He did, and I love him -

645
00:50:21,330 --> 00:50:24,832
- and I love you too, and I love
being able to tell you the truth.

646
00:50:25,125 --> 00:50:27,073
And I love...

647
00:50:27,074 --> 00:50:31,422
Faith, loyalty and all that shit, even now.

648
00:50:32,424 --> 00:50:33,758
And this?

649
00:50:35,427 --> 00:50:36,819
This?

650
00:50:38,973 --> 00:50:42,225
I don't know that this would be
what it is on its own.

651
00:50:43,269 --> 00:50:47,405
This is only what it is, because
it's something that's between -

652
00:50:47,731 --> 00:50:52,485
- me, my marriage to Michael,
you and your set of things.

653
00:50:52,406 --> 00:50:54,240
Does Andy have anything to drink?

654
00:51:01,665 --> 00:51:04,458
What are my things?
Nothing, I'm criticizing.

655
00:51:04,710 --> 00:51:06,049
I'm just...

656
00:51:06,550 --> 00:51:09,589
I know that if we went for it,
we'd lose it.

657
00:51:10,007 --> 00:51:13,259
That's hard to lose,
because we never wear out.

658
00:51:13,385 --> 00:51:16,596
We were just getting to know,
that we weren't right for each other.

659
00:51:16,722 --> 00:51:18,115
You didn't want to!

660
00:51:18,116 --> 00:51:20,308
No.
No?

661
00:51:20,851 --> 00:51:23,185
I came to Paris for two months!

662
00:51:23,478 --> 00:51:24,787
You do hold that against me.

663
00:51:24,813 --> 00:51:28,941
I don't hold anything against you!
I was finishing a book.

664
00:51:29,651 --> 00:51:30,998
I was too tired to figure out -

665
00:51:30,999 --> 00:51:32,903
what you being there even meant.

666
00:51:33,030 --> 00:51:36,782
It should have meant that you wanted
to spend some time with me.

667
00:51:37,701 --> 00:51:41,370
It doesn't matter.
No, it matters to me.

668
00:51:42,039 --> 00:51:44,332
Because I'm the one
who has to see you here.

669
00:51:44,583 --> 00:51:46,667
I'm the one who has to look around Andy's

670
00:51:46,793 --> 00:51:49,128
to see these pictures of you in this life.

671
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,392
What?

672
00:51:48,793 --> 00:51:51,503
I was what you needed
to be sure of Michael?

673
00:51:52,714 --> 00:51:56,383
No. No.
It doesn't work like that.

674
00:52:01,347 --> 00:52:03,015
I think...

675
00:52:04,601 --> 00:52:08,604
Maybe I've never wanted this to change.

676
00:52:09,272 --> 00:52:10,772
Everything...

677
00:52:11,482 --> 00:52:16,111
Everything changes, but this,
this still hasn't.

678
00:52:16,280 --> 00:52:19,240
Not for me.
That's a lesson.

679
00:52:20,993 --> 00:52:24,162
I saw you this morning...

680
00:52:28,125 --> 00:52:32,211
And... in the middle of most nights,
when I can't sleep -

681
00:52:33,505 --> 00:52:35,381
I still replay you.

682
00:53:00,576 --> 00:53:02,369
I'm going to take her out for a walk.

683
00:53:51,462 --> 00:53:53,005
Keys, Alex!

684
00:53:54,048 --> 00:53:56,967
I thought you took them with you.
No.

685
00:53:57,719 --> 00:53:59,219
Oh merde!

686
00:53:59,512 --> 00:54:01,096
Did you leave them upstairs?

687
00:54:01,222 --> 00:54:03,807
Yeah, can we call someone?

688
00:54:05,433 --> 00:54:07,602
We can call Caroline, but...

689
00:54:15,101 --> 00:54:16,486
Shit!

690
00:55:14,549 --> 00:55:18,252
Give me that, I'll give it back to you tomorrow.
Let's go.

691
00:55:50,669 --> 00:55:53,295
You weren't lying about the dog!
No!

692
00:55:54,756 --> 00:55:56,473
Come with me.
Let us find Fred.

693
00:55:56,474 --> 00:55:57,791
Okay.

694
00:56:01,884 --> 00:56:05,511
Her husband's best friend's dog.

695
00:56:12,607 --> 00:56:16,235
She's the one Chris told me about?
I don't know.

696
00:56:16,361 --> 00:56:20,614
At Phillips wedding, after
you just broken off with Lauren.

697
00:56:21,575 --> 00:56:24,785
I asked him, what the hell was
wrong with you.

698
00:56:27,164 --> 00:56:28,706
I liked Lauren.

699
00:56:29,416 --> 00:56:32,418
But I like this one much more.

700
00:56:34,239 --> 00:56:37,320
She's smart.
Yeah.

701
00:56:37,355 --> 00:56:39,049
She's funny.
Yeah.

702
00:56:39,050 --> 00:56:41,550
She's gorgeous!
I know.

703
00:56:43,101 --> 00:56:44,451
And she's honest.

704
00:56:45,390 --> 00:56:48,726
Well I mean, besides the fact she's out with you,
and her husband is out of town.

705
00:56:49,978 --> 00:56:51,520
But she's married.

706
00:56:52,814 --> 00:56:56,817
I know.
No, you don't. No, you've never been married.

707
00:56:57,027 --> 00:56:58,999
I mean fuck the vows.

708
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:01,572
It's the years you can't undo.

709
00:57:02,073 --> 00:57:06,285
You will never be able to take her away
the years with her husband.

710
00:57:06,453 --> 00:57:11,207
And the moment you try, this,
this will be gone.

711
00:57:12,499 --> 00:57:15,753
Trust me.
That would be a shame.

712
00:57:19,132 --> 00:57:23,052
I bet you've had less than a hundred days
together, am I right?

713
00:57:25,784 --> 00:57:27,153
It's the best.

714
00:57:29,893 --> 00:57:33,979
Be smart.
Keep it as it is.

715
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,305
I'm in!

716
00:58:22,206 --> 00:58:23,510
Your turn.

717
00:58:30,135 --> 00:58:31,527
Here.

718
00:58:34,514 --> 00:58:36,182
Oh, come on.

719
00:58:36,433 --> 00:58:38,976
I'm not going to be the only one in here,
in my underwear.

720
00:59:35,000 --> 00:59:36,750
You're uncomfortable.

721
00:59:37,377 --> 00:59:39,253
I am uncomfortable.

722
00:59:41,590 --> 00:59:43,424
You don't hold back much, do you?

723
00:59:43,550 --> 00:59:47,136
We're here in our underwear. I think
it's a late for that, no?

724
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:47,168
Do you remember that first night?

725
01:00:47,961 --> 01:00:49,503
Do you ever think about it?

726
01:00:50,339 --> 01:00:51,647
Of course I do.

727
01:00:54,259 --> 01:00:57,553
I did not want to go home,
and you put me in a taxi.

728
01:00:59,106 --> 01:01:00,489
And do you remember that night -

729
01:01:00,515 --> 01:01:03,284
- when we met the photographer
you were interviewing?

730
01:01:03,310 --> 01:01:05,436
And he was drunk!
He was drunk.

731
01:01:07,397 --> 01:01:10,149
And you danced on that
top of yours with no back.

732
01:01:13,237 --> 01:01:14,695
Come.

733
01:02:19,303 --> 01:02:20,720
Let's go.

734
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:17,002
So, have you ever been cheated on?

735
01:03:19,548 --> 01:03:20,898
No.

736
01:03:25,387 --> 01:03:26,971
Well, I have.

737
01:03:30,642 --> 01:03:33,227
The worst part with her I found out.

738
01:03:36,439 --> 01:03:39,275
We shared a photo account -

739
01:03:39,401 --> 01:03:42,361
- and I went on the website to order
some pictures -

740
01:03:42,696 --> 01:03:46,198
- and I saw the album she decided to
share with him.

741
01:03:47,075 --> 01:03:50,536
I think they were together
for the weekend, or something.

742
01:03:51,030 --> 01:03:54,415
I could have done without the visuals.

743
01:03:54,875 --> 01:03:59,086
There was this one,
they were laughing so hard...

744
01:04:00,000 --> 01:04:01,459
What happened?

745
01:04:01,585 --> 01:04:06,005
We fought like animals
for about a month and...

746
01:04:07,215 --> 01:04:09,264
I was angry...

747
01:04:09,765 --> 01:04:13,513
Maybe because I thought I had to be.

748
01:04:14,640 --> 01:04:16,557
Or maybe because I was sad.

749
01:04:17,434 --> 01:04:21,521
But he still wanted to be with me,
I still wanted to be with him.

750
01:04:21,897 --> 01:04:23,247
So what happened?

751
01:04:24,400 --> 01:04:26,109
We stayed together -

752
01:04:27,000 --> 01:04:29,208
had the best year of our relationship.

753
01:04:31,653 --> 01:04:33,045
And then?

754
01:04:37,367 --> 01:04:38,717
He died.

755
01:04:40,787 --> 01:04:42,154
I'm sorry.

756
01:04:58,391 --> 01:05:01,893
Do you want anything to drink?
No, I'm fine.

757
01:05:24,125 --> 01:05:26,334
Do you think you still
would have been with him?

758
01:05:29,839 --> 01:05:33,550
Yeah, definitely.

759
01:05:36,554 --> 01:05:40,515
And I think I'd still be
here, attracted to you.

760
01:06:08,000 --> 01:06:10,168
You'd never guess what I was upset about
this morning.

761
01:06:11,211 --> 01:06:14,380
Michael had a work think last night
that we went to -

762
01:06:15,257 --> 01:06:18,801
- and I was accusing him of being
attracted to this woman he's working with.

763
01:06:19,595 --> 01:06:21,763
Was he?
I think so.

764
01:06:23,474 --> 01:06:25,433
You think there's something going on?

765
01:06:25,726 --> 01:06:27,252
It could be.

766
01:06:28,053 --> 01:06:29,979
I think he'd want that to be.

767
01:06:32,281 --> 01:06:34,480
He's in Philadelphia with her right now.

768
01:06:35,235 --> 01:06:36,778
Are you worried?

769
01:06:38,447 --> 01:06:40,306
I think I make too big
a deal out of it.

770
01:06:40,307 --> 01:06:41,665
Why?

771
01:06:43,243 --> 01:06:45,703
It's 2:00 in the morning and
I'm here with you.

772
01:06:50,250 --> 01:06:53,931
So when you think you could get up and have
absolutely no idea what a day will go?

773
01:06:54,379 --> 01:06:55,797
Eighty...

774
01:06:56,215 --> 01:06:59,967
Ninety... a thousand go by
without incident -

775
01:07:00,094 --> 01:07:01,719
and then all of a sudden...

776
01:07:02,262 --> 01:07:04,597
Hello!
Hello!

777
01:07:06,850 --> 01:07:09,352
What if I hadn't come up for
coffee this morning?

778
01:07:10,395 --> 01:07:12,271
I would have called.

779
01:07:12,940 --> 01:07:15,066
If my number changed?

780
01:07:16,610 --> 01:07:18,569
I would have come upstairs.

781
01:07:19,571 --> 01:07:21,155
What about Michael?

782
01:07:27,165 --> 01:07:29,416
Why did you stop e-mailing me?

783
01:07:35,298 --> 01:07:37,258
Because it wasn't enough...

784
01:07:41,596 --> 01:07:45,349
Do you know how often I have to
make a choice, not to write.

785
01:07:46,059 --> 01:07:48,269
"Hello, Alex. How are you?"

786
01:07:48,270 --> 01:07:50,479
"Where are you? What are you doing?"

787
01:07:51,481 --> 01:07:55,276
"Do you want to meet me?
Whatever".

788
01:07:56,153 --> 01:07:58,154
"This Friday for dinner?"

789
01:07:59,030 --> 01:08:01,031
"Just to catch up".

790
01:08:05,620 --> 01:08:08,539
You really touch me whenever
you feel like, don't you?

791
01:08:09,082 --> 01:08:10,499
No, I don't.

792
01:08:11,877 --> 01:08:16,046
I touch you a fraction of how
often I'd like to.

793
01:08:17,674 --> 01:08:18,983
Why?

794
01:08:23,180 --> 01:08:24,889
Because I like you.

795
01:08:40,284 --> 01:08:41,910
I can't.

796
01:08:46,832 --> 01:08:50,835
I can't do anymore,
and look him in the eye.

797
01:09:03,641 --> 01:09:07,435
You just told me he's away with
a woman you got upset about.

798
01:09:12,024 --> 01:09:14,275
Michael isn't doing anything...

799
01:09:30,292 --> 01:09:32,877
I never told him about us.

800
01:09:34,088 --> 01:09:35,427
Even when -

801
01:09:36,267 --> 01:09:38,967
I found the need to confess something.

802
01:09:39,134 --> 01:09:40,468
Which is when?

803
01:09:41,720 --> 01:09:43,930
When I'm drunk, or happy -

804
01:09:45,349 --> 01:09:47,767
or after a fight, or in the middle of one -

805
01:09:47,893 --> 01:09:50,561
when things slip out, this never does.

806
01:09:50,688 --> 01:09:52,939
Why?
Would he be angry?

807
01:09:53,901 --> 01:09:55,860
He'd have no right to be.

808
01:09:57,196 --> 01:09:58,738
I gave you up.

809
01:10:12,128 --> 01:10:13,795
So what's Helen like?

810
01:10:30,438 --> 01:10:32,314
We have another couple of hours -

811
01:10:33,274 --> 01:10:35,275
- I don't want to spend them talking
about Helen.

812
01:10:37,945 --> 01:10:39,404
Come on...

813
01:10:42,692 --> 01:10:46,467
come
 here.

814
01:13:36,050 --> 01:13:39,010
What time is it?
Six thirty.

815
01:14:06,539 --> 01:14:07,914
Laura...

816
01:14:08,082 --> 01:14:11,793
Michael, I don't need us to talk about it.

817
01:14:14,338 --> 01:14:16,589
Last night...
Michael, please.

818
01:14:17,758 --> 01:14:19,133
Just don't.

819
01:14:24,265 --> 01:14:26,307
I didn't think that would happen.

820
01:14:27,061 --> 01:14:28,853
Not even a second time?

821
01:15:37,000 --> 01:15:39,712
Well there's so much going on
right now, isn't it?

822
01:15:46,498 --> 01:15:49,458
What I wouldn't give to have tired
of you.

823
01:15:57,092 --> 01:16:00,186
Let me drop you off.
No, I'd rather walk.

824
01:16:00,295 --> 01:16:02,271
Are you sure?
Yes, it would be good for her.

825
01:16:02,272 --> 01:16:03,647
It would be good for me.

826
01:16:05,559 --> 01:16:09,020
Let's not do this in a big way, ok?
Please.

827
01:16:16,862 --> 01:16:18,279
See ya!

828
01:17:41,000 --> 01:17:42,793
<i>It's possible I overreacted.</i>

829
01:17:42,794 --> 01:17:44,187
<i>I know that. I know you.</i>

830
01:17:44,188 --> 01:17:45,574
<i>And I love you.
Jo.</i>

831
01:18:27,074 --> 01:18:28,825
Hey Andy, it's me.

832
01:18:30,828 --> 01:18:32,704
I need you to cover for me.

833
01:19:09,369 --> 01:19:11,120
Hey.
Hey.

834
01:19:11,246 --> 01:19:13,539
Are you ready?
Yeah. Where's Michael?

835
01:19:14,304 --> 01:19:15,804
He had to go back to New York.

836
01:19:17,010 --> 01:19:18,405
Is everything ok?

837
01:19:18,478 --> 01:19:21,063
Yeah, he left me a voicemail.

838
01:19:21,089 --> 01:19:23,215
I guess, Stuart needed him
to go back.

839
01:19:24,842 --> 01:19:26,218
Okay...

840
01:19:26,345 --> 01:19:27,845
I'll see you out front.

841
01:21:18,248 --> 01:21:19,557
Joey...

842
01:21:19,963 --> 01:21:21,589
What are you doing back?

843
01:21:22,716 --> 01:21:24,383
What's Lucy doing here?

844
01:21:25,343 --> 01:21:27,678
We got locked out of Andy's.

845
01:21:27,846 --> 01:21:30,306
Who?
Me and Lucy.

846
01:21:31,516 --> 01:21:32,850
When?

847
01:21:34,561 --> 01:21:39,482
Last night, when I went over to walk her.

848
01:21:40,066 --> 01:21:41,692
You've been crying, Joey?

849
01:21:42,777 --> 01:21:44,153
A bit.

850
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:46,792
What are you doing back?

851
01:21:49,254 --> 01:21:50,963
We finished up early.

852
01:21:52,341 --> 01:21:54,675
Thought the presentation was today?

853
01:21:54,801 --> 01:21:57,720
No, we finished up early.

854
01:22:04,311 --> 01:22:06,145
I'm sorry about our fight.

855
01:22:09,399 --> 01:22:11,067
Yeah, so am I.

856
01:22:13,111 --> 01:22:16,239
Let's not talk about it, okay?

857
01:22:16,865 --> 01:22:22,078
Let's have a great lunch, let's walk.

858
01:22:22,871 --> 01:22:24,455
Let's make a day of it.

859
01:22:26,583 --> 01:22:27,917
Okay.

860
01:22:30,587 --> 01:22:31,963
Does she want to go out?

861
01:22:32,089 --> 01:22:33,881
Probably.

862
01:22:34,007 --> 01:22:37,134
I'll take her.
Come on.

863
01:22:48,063 --> 01:22:51,148
Are you okay?
Yeah.

864
01:23:03,537 --> 01:23:05,162
I love you.

865
01:23:35,063 --> 01:23:40,063
SUBTITLE BY: DUQA

